# Publisher

This is an actor that represents external companies who publish and distribute books that WebBooks sells.
WebBooks obtains both physical copies of Print media and publisher keys for eBooks from teh relevant Publisher.
While actor classes generally don't have state models, this is a relatively rare 
exception in that it does have behavior relevant to WebBooks processes. That behavior is shown in the 
state diagram, and the remainder of the behavior is outside the scope of Order Fulfillment.

◇

actor_key: publisher

attributes:
    name:
        name: "name"
        details: The name of the Publisher--how they would like to be referred to--such as "Permanent Press" or "JKL Publishing House".
        rules: unconstrained
        index_nums: [0] # Index zero is "key"
    email:
        name: "email address"
        index_nums: [1]
        details: |
            The address that will be used for all (email) communication between this Publisher and WebBooks. Publishers may
            have more than one email address, but they must select only one of them for primary communication with WebBooks.
        rules: any valid email address acoording to relevant IETF specifications
    address:
        name: "postal address"
        details: |
            The primary postal mailing address of the publsiher. A publisher may have more than one valid postal 
            mailing address but must choose only one to be their primary contact mailing address.
        rules: any mailing address acceptable to the US Post Office and Canada Post

associations:

    - name: Fills
      from_multiplicity: "1"
      to_class_key: 01_order_fulfillment/replenish_order
      to_multiplicity: "any"


states:

  Exists:
    details: The publisher is in the system.

events:

    "«new»":
        details: Create this publisher.
        parameters:
            - name: name
              source: somewhere
            - name: email
              source: somewhere
            - name: address
              source: somewhere

    "Replenish":
        details: Send new media to WebBooks.
        parameters:
            - name: medium
              source: somewhere
            - name: qty
              source: somewhere

    "PlaceOrder":
        details: WebBooks orders new media from Publisher.
        parameters:
            - name: order id
              source: somewhere
            - name: collection of (isbn, qty)
              source: somewhere


actions:

    Initialize:
        details: Add a new medium to the system.
        requires:
            - email is consistent with the range of .email address
            - address is consistent with the range of .postal address
        guarantees:
            - |
                one new Publisher exists with:
                    .name == name
                    .email == email
                    .postal address == address

    MakeOrAddToOrder:
        details: Remove some of this medium from the inventory.
        guarantees:
            - |
                if no open Replenish order already exists for this Publsiher via Fills 
                    then new (Print medium, qty) has been signaled 
                    otherwise add (Print medium, qty) has been signaled
                    for that open Replenish order via Fills

    ProcessOrderPlacement:
        details: Add more of this medium to the inventory.
        guarantees:
            - |
                Publisher is aware of the contents of the Replenish order via Fills
                    (note: this is really external, it's shown for completeness in this model)

transitions:

    - {from: "", event: "«new»", to: "Exists", action: "Initialize"}
    - {from: "Exists", event: "Replenish", to: "Exists", action: "MakeOrAddToOrder"}
    - {from: "Exists", event: "PlaceOrder", to: "Exists", action: "ProcessOrderPlacement"}
